      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DARCY DAKOTA (7) broke from a low draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only a nose (19.53) behind Wicket at this track. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Top prospect. SUMMER MOUSE (1) jumps from the inside draw. Latest effort finished 4th on July 9 over 457m at this track behind Zipping Tesfay beaten 7 lengths (26.04) in a Grade 5. With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. PROFESSOR SAMSON (2) turned in a plain effort last time when sixth at Capalaba over 366m behind In Absentia (20.25) in a Mix 5. Was in the money prior to that. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. BAD AND BERTHA (4) is building a nice sequence of placings – must be respected.",
